</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[227,1437,711,878]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicName authority="Ustjuzhanin &amp; Kovtunovich" authorityName="Ustjuzhanin &amp; Kovtunovich" authorityYear="2016" box="[227,777,711,737]" class="Insecta" family="Pterophoridae" genus="Platyptilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stanleyi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[227,446,711,737]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Platyptilia stanleyi</emphasis>
Ustjuzhanin &amp; Kovtunovich
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[782,869,712,738]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished by its giant wingspan, which is unique among all the species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fetcheri Ustjuzhanin &amp; Kovtunovich" authorityYear="2016" box="[750,874,746,772]" class="Insecta" family="Pterophoridae" genus="Platyptilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[750,874,746,772]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Platyptilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as well as among all the African 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zeller" authorityYear="1841" box="[1264,1433,746,772]" class="Insecta" family="Pterophoridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pterophoridae</taxonomicName>
. In the male genitalia the new species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Fetcheri Ustjuzhanin &amp; Kovtunovich" authorityName="Fetcheri Ustjuzhanin &amp; Kovtunovich" authorityYear="2016" box="[783,1347,781,808]" class="Insecta" family="Pterophoridae" genus="Platyptilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="sp.nov.">
<emphasis box="[783,1010,781,807]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Platyptilia Fetcheri</emphasis>
Ustjuzhanin &amp; Kovtunovich
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1353,1437,782,808]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" rank="species">sp.nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in the shape of the phallus and uncus, but clearly differs from it by the short and wide anellus arms and the fold on the inner side of the sacculus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[227,362,911,937]" box="[227,362,911,937]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
